## Code Conventions

- **TypeScript strict mode** ‚Äî zero errors from `npx tsc --noEmit`
- **Never use `any`** ‚Äî use `unknown` + type guards
- **Named exports only** ‚Äî no default exports
- **Functional components only** ‚Äî no class components
- **Path aliases:** `@/` maps to `src/`
- **Props interfaces:** named `{Component}Props`

### Import Order

1. React
2. External libraries
3. Internal modules (`@/components/`, `@/lib/`, etc.)
4. Types

### Naming

| What | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `ReservationCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase, use- prefix | `useReservations.ts` |
| Services | camelCase, -service suffix | `reservation-service.ts` |
| Types | PascalCase | `Reservation` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_PAGE_SIZE` |
| DB tables | snake_case | `reservations` |
| DB columns | snake_case | `check_in_date` |
| API routes | kebab-case | `/api/fxl/entities` |

### Commit Convention

- `feat: [description]` ‚Äî new feature
- `fix: [description]` ‚Äî bug fix
- `refactor: [description]` ‚Äî code cleanup
- `chore: [description]` ‚Äî config, tooling

---

## Security Rules

- ALL secrets in `.env.local` (NEVER committed)
- Client-side env vars prefixed with `VITE_`
- Clerk JWT validated on every API request
- `org_id` extracted from server-validated JWT (never from client)
- RLS enabled on EVERY Supabase table
- Every table has `org_id text NOT NULL` column
- Security headers set in `vercel.json`

---

## FXL Contract

This app exposes these endpoints for the FXL Core Hub:

| Endpoint | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| GET /api/fxl/manifest | App metadata, entities, widgets |
| GET /api/fxl/entities/:type | Paginated entity list |
| GET /api/fxl/entities/:type/:id | Single entity |
| GET /api/fxl/widgets/:id/data | Widget data |
| GET /api/fxl/search?q= | Cross-entity search |
| GET /api/fxl/health | Health + contract version |

Contract is v1 (read-only). All entity endpoints filter by `org_id`.

